    <collapsible title="What information is collected?">
      <p>We respect your ability to choose how your information is used, so in most instances you are able to opt out of providing most of the following information through your user settings. When registering for Wago.io, using Wago.io, and participating in our services, we collect certain data in order to provide you with the best possible experience. This includes information that identifies, relates to, describes, references, is capable of being associated with, or could reasonably be linked, directly or indirectly, with a particular consumer or device (“Personal Information”).  Such Personal Information includes your name, email address, and battletag.</p><p>A list of general information we collect, and its purpose can be found below:</p><ul><li>Operational information that is needed for essential base functionality associated with Wago.io, including installed applications, subscriptions, privacy setting, IP address, and other related information.</li><li>Optional information provided by you to customize Wago.io to your preferences and setting. This helps ensure you can use Wago.io the way that best works for you. You have the option to opt out of providing this information.</li><li>Optional data used to track performance, service, connection, and stability, including base computer hardware and software settings. Our ability to monitor this information helps us optimize Wago.io for our users.  You have the option to opt out of providing this information.</li><li>Optional information associated with user account creation on Wago.io. If you prefer not to create a Wago.io account, you can refrain from creating an account. You have the option to opt out of providing this information.</li><li>Billing information if you opt to use paid services associated with Wago.io.</li><li>Optional website analytics associated with your use of Wago.io, including pageviews, clicks, scrolling, browser type, domain names, access times, referring website addresses, and other associated information. We do this in order to determine what Wago.io services are the most popular, maintain quality of service, and to generate usage statistics. This data is used to deliver customized content and advertising within Wago.io to customers whose behavior indicates that they are interested in a particular subject area. You have the option to opt out of providing this information.</li><li>Optional social media information if you choose to link your Battle.net, Discord, Google, Patreon, or Twitter account to assist in user account management.</li></ul>
